# Level Up Game Merch Store

Spring Boot **2.7.18** (Java **17**) — **Milestone 2**

## Run locally
1. JDK 17 installed and selected in STS (Window → Preferences → Java → Installed JREs).
2. Import: **File → Import → Git → Projects from Git (with URI)** → paste the repo URL.
3. **Maven → Update Project** (Force Update) → **Project → Clean**.
4. **Run As → Spring Boot App**.
5. App will be available at `http://localhost:8080/` (after MVC pages are added).

## Demo account (seed)
- Email: `demo@clc.com`  
- Password: `pass1234`  
- Username: `demo`

## Project structure (M2)
- `com.clc.levelup.dto` — `UserRegistration`, `LoginRequest`
- `com.clc.levelup.validation` — `@PasswordMatches`, `PasswordMatchesValidator`
- `com.clc.levelup.model` — `User`
- `com.clc.levelup.service` — `UserService`, `AuthService` + in-memory impls
- `com.clc.levelup.config` — `MessageConfig`, `DataSeed` (optional)
- (MVC controllers + Thymeleaf views will be added by the UI role)

## Milestone 2 scope (team split)
**Mikkos (completed):**
- DTOs & validation (including cross-field validator)
- Domain model (`User`)
- In-memory services (`InMemoryUserService`, `InMemoryAuthService`)
- Validation messages & MessageSource config
- Optional seed user

**Jacob (completed):**
- Spring MVC controllers (Home, Register, Login/Logout, Products)
- Thymeleaf layout & fragments, pages (Bootstrap 5)
- Responsive check (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Screencast + Design Report updates

## Workflow
- Default branch: `master`
- Use feature branches → open Pull Requests into `master`
- Example: `feature/m2-ui-controllers-jacob`

## Tech notes
- **No DB in M2** (data in memory; resets on restart)
- Session key: `"principal"` after login (used to toggle navbar)
- Message keys: `user.email.exists`, `user.username.exists`, `auth.invalid`, `validation.passwords.mismatch`

